'''Hyperprothrombinemia''' is a state of high of [[prothrombin]] levels in the blood<ref>[http://www.merriam-webster.com/medical/hyperprothrombinemia Hyperprothrombinemia] Merriam Webster Dictionary. Accessed January 19, 2012.</ref> which leads to [[hypercoagulability]]. An example of a genetic cause includes the mutation [[prothrombin G20210A]].
